# .cursorrules — SEO Constitution for Shine Speech Pathology Website

> These rules apply to EVERY agent working on this project. They are non-negotiable.
> If any design decision, styling choice, or refactor would violate these rules, the rule wins.
> Read this file before every task.

---

## RULE 1: CONTENT VISIBILITY — NO HIDDEN CONTENT

Google's crawler cannot click or hover. Content behind accordions, tabs, "read more" toggles, or any interaction-dependent UI is devalued.

- All FAQ content must be fully visible on page load. No accordions. No collapsed sections.
- No "read more" truncation on any text block.
- No tab interfaces that hide page content.
- Dropdown navigation menus are fine (navigation, not content).

## RULE 2: ONE H1 PER PAGE

- Every page gets exactly one `<h1>` tag.
- H1 must contain the target keyword naturally.
- Homepage H1 is outcome-focused and parent-facing — NOT the business name.
- Never put the business name in an H1.

## RULE 3: HEADING HIERARCHY

- H1 → H2 → H3 → H4. Never skip levels.
- Never use heading tags for visual styling. Use CSS classes instead.

## RULE 4: INTERNAL LINKING

- Never repeat anchor text across the site. Every internal link uses unique text.
- Anchor text must describe the destination page (not "click here").
- Internal links belong in body paragraph content — not in headings, sidebars, or footers (nav links excepted).
- Don't use the brand name as anchor text for internal links.
- Minimum 3 contextual internal links per page in body content.

## RULE 5: SCHEMA ARCHITECTURE

This is a Service Area Business (SAB) with no physical clinic.

| Schema Type     | Placement                                    |
| --------------- | -------------------------------------------- |
| Organization    | `<head>` of EVERY page (identical markup)    |
| MedicalBusiness | Homepage ONLY (this is the GBP landing page) |
| Service         | Each condition page + each service-type page |
| FAQPage         | Any page with visible FAQ content            |
| BreadcrumbList  | Every page                                   |

- Do NOT put LocalBusiness or MedicalBusiness schema on any page except the homepage.
- Do NOT include streetAddress in schema (SAB hides address). Use areaServed instead.
- NAP (name, phone, email) must be identical everywhere: schema, header, footer, page content.

## RULE 6: URL FORMAT

```
/speech-therapy-[condition]-sydney-nsw        ← condition pages
/speech-pathologist-[suburb]-nsw              ← suburb pages
/[service-type]-speech-therapy-sydney-nsw     ← service/funding pages
```

Lowercase, hyphen-separated, no trailing slashes.

## RULE 7: META TAGS

- Title: unique per page, under 60 characters, includes primary keyword.
- Description: unique per page, 150-160 characters, includes location.
- No two pages share the same title or description.

## RULE 8: TECHNICAL SEO

- Self-referencing canonical tag on every page.
- Open Graph tags on every page (og:title, og:description, og:image, og:url).
- `<html lang="en">` (or `lang="zh"` for Chinese pages).
- All images: descriptive alt text, width/height attributes, lazy load below fold, WebP preferred.
- All phone numbers must be click-to-call (`tel:` links).
- ScrollToTop component resets scroll position on every route change.
- No orphan pages. Every page reachable via navigation or internal links.
- No broken links. No `<a href="#">` placeholders — use real routes or HTML comments.

## RULE 9: GOAL COMPLETION HIERARCHY

Homepage section order is MANDATORY. Proof and credibility come FIRST, educational content LAST:

1. Hero (solve my problem)
2. Trust signals (why trust you)
3. Services/conditions (do you handle my need)
4. Differentiators (why pick you)
5. How it works (process)
6. About/credentials (who are you)
7. Social proof (do others trust you)
8. Coordinator section (B2B audience)
9. FAQ (answer remaining concerns)
10. Service area + final CTA

Do NOT put About Us, company history, or educational content above proof/credibility sections.

## RULE 10: E-E-A-T (YMYL SITE)

This is a health website. Google applies its highest quality standards.

- Author attribution on every page: "Written by [Shine], Certified Practising Speech Pathologist" linking to /about.
- Real therapist photos only (use placeholders with `<!-- REPLACE: description -->` comments). No stock photos.
- Credentials must be visible (not collapsed) on About page and homepage.
- Video embed placeholder on About page.
- Social media links (LinkedIn minimum).

## RULE 11: DO NOT MODIFY

When styling or refactoring, NEVER change:

- HTML tag types (don't change an h2 to a div for styling)
- Schema markup (don't move, edit, or remove JSON-LD blocks)
- Meta tags (title, description, canonical, OG tags)
- Internal link href values or anchor text
- Heading hierarchy or heading content
- Alt text on images
- Form field names, types, or required attributes
- URL/route paths
- Content order on the homepage
